## Anti-patterns

- ❌ Treating `JOIN` clauses as the source of every column. Use SELECT-list alias prefix.
- ❌ Treating a CTE name as a physical input. Expand CTEs to their physical sources via `_resolve_terminal_upstreams`.
- ❌ Inventing predicate values. The formula MUST be a faithful (alias-resolved, whitespace-normalized) transcription of the SQL.
- ❌ Skipping columns that don't match the AS pattern. Try implicit-alias bare-column matching too.
- ❌ Emitting a formula for a column that the parser couldn't locate — emit `formula: null, reason: ...` instead.
